=====Usage notes=====
* For Hokkien, Taiwan's Ministry of Education recommends {{zh-l|*个}} for the general classifier ''ê'' and {{zh-l|*的}} for the possessive particle ''ê'', reserving {{zh-l|*個}} for the month classifier ''kò''.
* For Hakka, Taiwan's Ministry of Education recommends {{zh-l|个}} for the possessive particle.
* In Cantonese, when used for "yuan/dollar", {{lang|zh|個}} is usually only used when followed by cents.
* Northern Wu languages can mark for tenses, as well as aspects. In Old Shanghainese, this is used to mark the past tense, as opposed to a perfect aspect. In etymological spellings, {{zh-l|*箇}} (={{zh-l|*搿}}) is reserved for demonstrative pronouns, {{zh-l|*个}} for the possessive particle, while {{zh-l|*個}} is only used as classifier ({{zh-l|*一個}} <sup>7</sup>iq-g(h)eq) or literary readings ({{zh-l|*個人}} <sup>5</sup>ku-gnin).

